                <body xml:id="ch4.sc4.1.00113">                        
                                <p><hi rend="initialcap">C</hi>ASE 113.—<name type="person" key="663">Private John Frink</name>,
                                                <name type="organization" key="671">Co. K, 40th N. J.</name>; age 19; admitted <date type="admit" when="1865-06-04">June 4, 1865</date>.  Typhoid
                                        fever.  Severe diarrhœa, gastric irritability and
                                        nervous disorder were the prominent phenomena.  Died <date type="death" when="1865-06-23">23d</date>.  <hi rend="italic">Post-mortem</hi> examination
                                        <date type="autopsy" when="1865-06-24">twenty-four hours after death</date>: The lungs were emphysematous;
                                        the small intestine much inflamed; the glands of Peyer
                                        congested; the spleen normal.——<hi rend="italic"><name type="hospital" key="189">Third Division
                                                  Hospital</name>, Alexandria, Va.</hi></p>                        
